commit.message:
Merge pull request #9 from isikyus/feature/refactor-text-renderer

Refactor text_renderer.js
Deduplicate room and door lookup code

Move RequireJS text plugin to vendor/

The better to exclude it from Code Climate.

Add RequireJS text plugin to repository

Since I'm now relying on it to load templates

Extract templates to their own files

And add missing text_renderer/templates.js file from last commit
Extract text templates to their own file
Factor out looking up doors and rooms by ID

Low-hanging text-renderer refactoring

* Remove unnecessary comma
* Remove semicolons after if statements
* Change == to ===
Remove unneeded comment

Merge pull request #8 from isikyus/feature/add-doors

Add doors via text UI

Still a lot of CodeClimate warnings; but it's cleaner than it was.
Split up MapController action listeners

Remove TODO about Room.getWalls

It's already a function on Room
Fix text UI setting room coords as strings

Define per-interaction rendering methods

These should probably be factored out to their own file(s) in the long run,
but this is at least a step in the right direction.

Try to deduplicate submit-button handlers

Seems like it might have broken adding doors,
but it could also be I didn't test my last commit enough.
Attempt to deduplicate door-direction cases
Test the room.getWalls method
Add TODO about removing doors with rooms
Fix allocation of IDs to new rooms

Create a Room type

So I can define methods on it, as I need this to clean up
code that works on particular walls of a room.

Currently breaks automatic ID allocation (see test)

Make adding door without changing position work

Even though a position was showing as selected, it wasn't saving since we hadn't updated the action.

Settle for simple door coordinates when adding

It would be nice to have a more detailed description, but I don't think that's the highest priority; this works.

Properly test for failing to add doors

It's possible for the new door ID to be 0, and !0 is true, so need to test for false explicitly

Fix wrong offset for east and west doors

These weren't covered by the tests (and probably should be tested somewhere)

Apply offset when creating doors east and south

They should be at coordinates just inside the wall, rather than directly on it.
Also fix remaining bugs in add-door test

Add diagnostic when adding a door fails

This shouldn't normally happen, because the calling code should only try to create them in valid locations
Extra test for adding doors in all directions

Add doors via text UI.

Still bugs due to not compensating for door direction.

Remember selected value for door position

Previously we were redrawing and erasing it after each change.

Get add-door form showing up correctly

* Add add-door button that displays it when clicked.
* List available locations for given door direction.
* Fix confusion between East and West in test (East = right, West = left, like on a map)
